<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-54-0532 </DOCNO><TEXT>A computer programme was developed for purposes of control in relationto traditional heating systems where renewable energy sources are utilized.For experimental purposes a heat pump based on solar and geothermal energywas used. The programme created makes it possible to view, on a PC computerscreen, the operation of the control system and thus makes individualadjustment possible, where lines contain no more than 70 characters.The programme is based on a system of modules, and is described, andshown, in detail. (AB).</TEXT></DOC>